OL,3,CQuarter of motorists affected by
OL,4,Cbright headlights have cut night
OL,5,Cdriving
OL,7,FThe survey also found that drivers
OL,8,Funder 35 (41%) are more likely to say
OL,9,Fheadlights are too bright, as are 38%
OL,10,Fof those who drive hatchbacks,
OL,11,Festates, or saloons, which sit lower
OL,12,Fon the road than SUVs.
OL,14,FAround 17% of night-time drivers say
OL,15,Fbright headlights make them feel
OL,16,Ffatigued, while 16% report headaches,
OL,17,Fmigraines or eye pain.
